fr.zelus.jarvis.io

Class IntentProvider<T extends JarvisModule>

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.zelus.jarvis.io.EventProvider<T>
      • fr.zelus.jarvis.io.IntentProvider<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the concrete JarvisModule subclass type containing the provider
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Runnable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DiscordIntentProvider, SlackIntentProvider

    public abstract class IntentProvider<T extends JarvisModule>
extends EventProvider<T>
    A specialised EventProvider that extracts RecognizedIntent from textual user inputs.

    This class wraps a DialogFlowApi instance that is used to extract RecognizedIntents from textual user inputs. Note that the DialogFlowApi instance is not directly accessible by subclasses to avoid uncontrolled accesses such as intent creation, removal, and context manipulation. Subclasses should use getRecognizedIntent(String, JarvisSession) to retrieve RecognizedIntents from textual user inputs.

    • Constructor Detail

      • IntentProvider

        public IntentProvider(T containingModule)
        Constructs a new IntentProvider from the provided jarvisCore.

        This constructor sets the internal DialogFlowApi instance that is used to parse user input and retrieve RecognizedIntents.

        Note: this constructor should be used by IntentProviders that do not require additional parameters to be initialized. In that case see IntentProvider(JarvisModule, Configuration).

        Parameters:
        containingModule - the JarvisModule containing this IntentProvider
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if the provided containingModule is null

      • IntentProvider

        public IntentProvider(T containingModule,
                      Configuration configuration)
        Constructs a new IntentProvider with the provided containingModule and configuration.

        This constructor sets the internal DialogFlowApi instance that is used to parse user input and retrieve RecognizedIntents.

        Note: this constructor will be called by jarvis internal engine when initializing the JarvisCore component. Subclasses implementing this constructor typically need additional parameters to be initialized, that can be provided in the configuration.

        Parameters:
        containingModule - the JarvisModule containing this IntentProvider
        configuration - the Configuration used to initialize the IntentProvider

    • Method Detail

      • getRecognizedIntent

        public final RecognizedIntent getRecognizedIntent(String input,
                                                  JarvisSession session)
        Returns the RecognizedIntent from the provided user input and session.

        This method wraps the access to the underlying DialogFlowApi, and avoid uncontrolled accesses to the DialogFlowApi from IntentProviders (such as intent creation, removal, and context manipulation).

        Parameters:
        input - the textual user input to extract the RecognizedIntent from
        session - the JarvisSession wrapping the underlying DialogFlow session
        Returns:
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if the provided text or session is null
        IllegalArgumentException - if the provided text is empty
        DialogFlowException - if the DialogFlowApi is shutdown or if an exception is thrown by the underlying DialogFlow engine
